THE MARTYROLOGY5.

The Martyrology as we have it has been so added to, that it is impossible to tell what part, if any, is really due to Bede. And there is much in it that one would willingly believe not to be Bede's——too much ecclesiastioal gloating over the physioal horrors of mar- tyrdom, and legends of the purely silly kind. On the so-called poetioal Martyrology, see below, p. clviii.
